<subSubSection pageId="163" pageNumber="164" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="163.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[673,795,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colimae">
<emphasis box="[673,795,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">A. colimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the mandible with the two upper teeth wider than others; the clypeus short, with the anterior margin without a median tooth, and the clypeal carina hardly distinct from the clypeus; the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the frons with a frontal sulcus; the ocelli small; the transverse pronotal carina incomplete; the mesopleural suture opened; the basivolsella straight and angled; and the aedeagus with the basal portion convex and slender, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[855,977,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colimae">
<emphasis box="[855,977,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">A. colimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the mandible with the teeth equally wide; the clypeus long, with the anterior margin with a median tooth, and the clypeal carina distinct from the clypeus; the antennal scrobe carinate, but weak; the frons without a frontal sulcus; the ocelli large; the transverse pronotal carina complete; the mesopleural suture closed; the basivolsela with an apical excavation at the inner margin and with a short basal projection; and the aedeagus with the basal portion angled and wide.
</paragraph>
